    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>People or corporate bodies who design and construct organs, which are complex aerophones consisting of one or more rows of individual pipes. They may also advise and supervise the installation of the larger types of organs.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079228/Grove Art Online (2008-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000030001/Sadie and Latham, Norton/Grove Concise Encyclopedia of Music (1988)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Aquellos que diseñan y construyen organos, a menudo también aconsejan y supervisan la instalación de los tipos de instrumentos de mayor tamaño.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Spanish</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000131/CDBP-SNPC</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000051034/TAA database (2000-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Zij die orgels ontwerpen en bouwen en ook vaak tijdens het installeren van de grotere modellen advies geven en toezicht houden.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Dutch</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000205/AAT-Ned</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000113770/AAT-Ned (1994-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>設計並製作管風琴者，他們也常在較大型管風琴的安裝工程中擔任顧問或監工。</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
